WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:04.670
Dre: <i>Christmas... the most
wonderful time of the year.</i>

00:04.672 --> 00:06.705
<i>A time for tree trimming,</i>

00:06.707 --> 00:09.274
<i>roaring fires, Christmas Carols,</i>

00:09.276 --> 00:12.111
<i>but most important, a time
to be with the ones you love.</i>

00:12.113 --> 00:14.046
<i>But some would argue</i>

00:14.048 --> 00:15.981
<i>it's become
overly commercialized,</i>

00:15.983 --> 00:17.649
<i>that it's all about stuff.</i>

00:17.651 --> 00:19.651
<i>To these people, I would say...</i>

00:19.653 --> 00:20.352
<i>"duh!"</i>

00:20.354 --> 00:22.654
♪♪

00:22.656 --> 00:25.157
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Let go of me! Ow!

00:25.159 --> 00:27.793
<i>In fact, no one loves stuff
more than me...</i>

00:27.795 --> 00:29.661
Oh, here we go.
Here we go.

00:29.663 --> 00:31.630
<i>Except for these four.</i>

00:31.632 --> 00:33.465
[ Indistinct shouting ]

00:33.467 --> 00:35.634
<i>In my house,
Christmas morning has become</i>

00:35.636 --> 00:37.369
<i>like a competitive
eating contest.</i>

00:37.371 --> 00:39.505
Man: It is running
neck and neck.

00:39.507 --> 00:41.507
Man ♪2: Unbelievable...
11 hot dogs after just a minute.

00:41.509 --> 00:42.808
♪♪

00:42.810 --> 00:44.243
Give me something else to open!

00:44.245 --> 00:46.245
I need it now!
Both: Stockings!

00:46.247 --> 00:47.880
Go!

00:47.882 --> 00:49.915
♪♪

00:49.917 --> 00:51.984
<i>Which is why it didn't come
as a total surprise</i>

00:51.986 --> 00:53.519
<i>to hear pop say...</i>

00:53.521 --> 00:55.921
Whoa. Ah.

00:55.923 --> 00:58.323
As usual, dummy,
you've overdone it...

00:58.325 --> 01:00.926
Took something beautiful
and turned it into crap.

01:00.928 --> 01:02.761
I'm taking over Christmas.

01:02.763 --> 01:05.097
Santa's got
a brand-new bag.

01:09.703 --> 01:12.438
Son, your black ass
has completely bought into

01:12.440 --> 01:14.440
this white-Christmas
nonsense.

01:14.442 --> 01:15.541
Mm-hmm.

01:15.543 --> 01:17.176
Buy them damn kids
anything they ask for.

01:17.178 --> 01:19.078
Hell, you even buy 'em things
they don't ask for!

01:19.080 --> 01:20.712
It's too much, son.

01:20.714 --> 01:23.282
Oh, so, they should
just be disappointed

01:23.284 --> 01:24.583
and wake up to nothing...
Like I did.

01:24.585 --> 01:26.051
Unh-unh-unh!

01:26.053 --> 01:28.887
There was always something
for you under the tree.

01:28.889 --> 01:31.423
It's heavy!

01:35.930 --> 01:37.196
It's pickles.

01:37.198 --> 01:38.964
Boy, you know you love pickles!

01:38.966 --> 01:40.265
Not for Christmas, I don't!

01:40.267 --> 01:41.366
Well, you ate 'em
like you loved 'em.

01:41.368 --> 01:43.235
- You do love pickles, babe.
- Bow!

01:43.237 --> 01:44.470
Y'all talking about
how my baby love pickles?

01:44.472 --> 01:45.737
Mama, we are not...
Mm-hmm.

01:45.739 --> 01:47.739
Can we stop talking about
pickles, please?!

01:47.741 --> 01:49.441
Fine! You the one
that loved 'em so much.

01:49.443 --> 01:51.276
The point is,
you've rotted your children

01:51.278 --> 01:53.278
from the inside out with
all the stuff you've given 'em.

01:53.280 --> 01:55.147
You've lost
the true meaning of Christmas.

01:55.149 --> 01:58.283
Which is Jesus!
He is the reason for the season.

01:58.285 --> 02:00.452
Well, I was going to say,
listening to Donny Hathaway

02:00.454 --> 02:02.621
and sipping on cutty sark
till you're out of cutty sark.

02:02.623 --> 02:04.456
Either way, your generation
has ruined it

02:04.458 --> 02:07.059
with too... Much... Stuff.

02:07.061 --> 02:08.894
Yeah,
too... Much... Stuff.

02:08.896 --> 02:11.230
Oh, so, it's<i> our</i> fault?

02:11.232 --> 02:14.066
Oh, hey, mama, uh,
what did the three wise men

02:14.068 --> 02:15.667
bring baby Jesus in his manger?

02:15.669 --> 02:17.236
Hmm?

02:17.238 --> 02:20.172
Oh, gold, frankincense [Murmurs]

02:20.174 --> 02:21.406
Speak up, mama,
'cause it sounded like

02:21.408 --> 02:24.176
you said stuff,
which I never got.

02:24.178 --> 02:26.111
Wait a minute.
H-h-hold on.

02:26.113 --> 02:29.915
Did you rise from the dead
and provide man with salvation?

02:29.917 --> 02:31.450
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

02:31.452 --> 02:32.985
Well, until you do<i> that,</i>

02:32.987 --> 02:35.521
you thank<i> god</i> for those pickles.

02:35.523 --> 02:37.122
Amen.

02:37.124 --> 02:38.524
You know, maybe Ruby and pops
are right, though.

02:38.526 --> 02:40.159
What?
When I was growing up,

02:40.161 --> 02:41.860
we used to have to
make our own gifts.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.629
Ooh, that sounds terrible.

02:43.631 --> 02:45.531
Yeah, stay in your Lane,
rainbow.

02:45.533 --> 02:47.466
No, I'm agreeing with you.

02:47.468 --> 02:49.801
Okay, all I'm saying
is that we could live

02:49.803 --> 02:51.603
with a little less stuff
in our lives.

02:51.605 --> 02:53.338
See that? Even your own wife
agrees with me.

02:53.340 --> 02:54.940
Okay.

02:54.942 --> 02:56.441
So, you're saying
I should return

02:56.443 --> 02:58.977
that Cartier juste un clou
bracelet that I bought you.

02:58.979 --> 03:01.113
The kids, Dre.
The kids can live on less.

03:01.115 --> 03:03.015
We're adults.
Oh, just for the babies.

03:03.017 --> 03:05.217
Now, did you say "bracelet"
or "bracelets"?

03:05.219 --> 03:06.852
'Cause, you know,
the whole stacking thing

03:06.854 --> 03:08.053
is trending right now.

03:08.055 --> 03:10.389
So it's best if you have
two or like three.

03:10.391 --> 03:11.723
Four really sells it.

03:11.725 --> 03:14.393
All I know is that I love
the look on my kids' faces

03:14.395 --> 03:16.328
when I give them
the perfect gift.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.197
Junior! Come here, junior.
Watch this.

03:18.199 --> 03:20.699
Will you tell pops how much
you love the skateboard

03:20.701 --> 03:22.067
I got you last Christmas.

03:22.069 --> 03:24.469
Oh, I traded that for a pizza.

03:24.471 --> 03:26.038
Get out.

03:26.040 --> 03:27.506
Oh, yeah, I bet his little face

03:27.508 --> 03:29.174
just lit up
when he ate that pizza.

03:29.176 --> 03:32.711
Speaking of gifts, we saw
the presents around the tree.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.313
It felt light.

03:34.315 --> 03:36.381
Real light,
like practice-run light.

03:36.383 --> 03:38.884
It's Christmas.
We got to play to win!

03:38.886 --> 03:41.553
Doing a bang-up job
there, son.

03:41.555 --> 03:44.189
<i>As much as I hate to admit it,
pops was right.</i>

03:44.191 --> 03:46.325
<i>My kids were monsters,</i>

03:46.327 --> 03:48.760
<i>who were about to get
a lot less stuff.</i>

03:48.762 --> 03:51.063
So, these gifts
that you were going to get

03:51.065 --> 03:52.264
are going in my trunk.

03:52.266 --> 03:55.334
And from now on,
you get one gift.

03:55.336 --> 03:56.568
Dear god!
Just kill me!

03:56.570 --> 03:57.869
Aw!
You broke my heart.

03:57.871 --> 04:00.105
Wait. One gift
for all of us to share?

04:00.107 --> 04:02.207
Now, that is
an interesting idea.

04:02.209 --> 04:03.342
Both: Shut up!

04:03.344 --> 04:05.010
What is wrong with you?!

04:05.012 --> 04:06.278
I'm just asking for clarity.

04:06.280 --> 04:08.547
No, you each get one gift.

04:08.549 --> 04:10.549
And I'm suggesting
something useful,

04:10.551 --> 04:13.952
like cold cuts, can of tuna,
honey-baked ham.

04:13.954 --> 04:15.254
My favorite. No, no.
What's going on?

04:15.256 --> 04:16.922
There's no sense in arguing.

04:16.924 --> 04:18.257
It's one gift

04:18.259 --> 04:20.892
and my traditional
Christmas Eve dinner.

04:20.894 --> 04:22.628
This is your new reality.

04:22.630 --> 04:25.197
And in the spirit
of taking less,

04:25.199 --> 04:27.766
we are all gonna
start volunteering more.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.434
Huh?
We're not doing that.

04:29.436 --> 04:32.537
There you go again...
Swerving out of your Lane.

04:32.539 --> 04:34.773
Dre, come on.
I backed up your one-gift idea.

04:34.775 --> 04:37.709
Yeah, because my idea
was a good one.

04:37.711 --> 04:39.478
Bow, come to me
with these half-baked ideas

04:39.480 --> 04:41.446
so I don't have to shoot you
down in front of the children.

04:41.448 --> 04:43.548
But you...
They lose respect for you.

04:43.550 --> 04:44.783
He's not wrong.

04:44.785 --> 04:47.119
Well, I'm gonna volunteer
because it's nice.

04:47.121 --> 04:48.787
Whatever.
One gift.

04:48.789 --> 04:51.089
That idea is real.

04:51.091 --> 04:52.658
Can our stockings be
our one gift?

04:52.660 --> 04:53.825
Both: Shut up!

04:53.827 --> 04:55.294
What is wrong with you?

04:55.296 --> 04:57.429
What do you guys have
against clarity?!

04:57.431 --> 04:59.164
♪♪

04:59.166 --> 05:01.400
One gift?!
This is an outrage!

05:01.402 --> 05:03.302
I think
I'll ask for a yo-yo.

05:03.304 --> 05:04.770
Is this a joke to you?

05:04.772 --> 05:06.104
Think bigger!

05:06.106 --> 05:08.807
But not too big.
Dad said no to a Tesla.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.275
Okay, so, we're looking
at something

05:10.277 --> 05:12.010
between yo-yo and Tesla.

05:12.012 --> 05:13.845
So, that's, like, a passat?

05:13.847 --> 05:15.280
Ugh.

05:15.282 --> 05:16.648
Uh, you guys are playing this
all wrong.

05:16.650 --> 05:18.617
If we're extra good,
they'll cave.

05:18.619 --> 05:19.918
They're cavers.

05:19.920 --> 05:21.687
We just have to play
to our strengths.

05:21.689 --> 05:24.690
Zoey, Jack, you'll be kind.

05:24.692 --> 05:26.024
I'll be helpful.

05:26.026 --> 05:28.493
And, junior...

05:28.495 --> 05:29.995
You'll disappear.

05:29.997 --> 05:30.829
Huh?

05:30.831 --> 05:32.998
Uh, trust me on this.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.133
Absence makes
the heart grow fonder.

05:35.135 --> 05:37.436
She's right.
Less of you is more.

05:37.438 --> 05:39.805
I-I'm not sure
about this.

05:39.807 --> 05:41.139
Well, you better get sure

05:41.141 --> 05:43.275
because you're this close
to waking up

05:43.277 --> 05:45.110
to a stocking
full of Turkey pastrami.

05:45.112 --> 05:48.113
Say no more.
I bid you adieu.

05:48.115 --> 05:50.449
Mm.
That was a great call.

05:50.451 --> 05:52.050
Felt right.

05:52.052 --> 05:54.553
<i>So, I went to work knowing
I was doing the right thing</i>

05:54.555 --> 05:56.021
<i>for my kids,</i>

05:56.023 --> 05:58.724
<i>but my co-workers didn't like
the one-gift idea.</i>

05:58.726 --> 05:59.891
You cheap bastard.

05:59.893 --> 06:01.393
No, no, no.

06:01.395 --> 06:04.396
It's because Christmas
is about more than stuff.

06:04.398 --> 06:05.697
Wait, what?

06:05.699 --> 06:09.634
Why would you...
Oh, it's a fear campaign.

06:09.636 --> 06:12.637
Imagine a world not about stuff.

06:12.639 --> 06:16.508
You're creating a panic and
offering a solution... genius!

06:16.510 --> 06:17.809
What?

06:17.811 --> 06:19.511
It's kind of like
when the saline companies and I

06:19.513 --> 06:22.414
created the flu vaccine
giving people the flu

06:22.416 --> 06:25.250
in order to combat the flu...
Hilarious!

06:25.252 --> 06:27.352
And when you lost that account
and created

06:27.354 --> 06:31.223
the "vaccines cause autism"
campaign... very strong!

06:31.225 --> 06:32.224
Aww, stop it.
Yes.

06:32.226 --> 06:33.692
Oh, god.

06:33.694 --> 06:36.395
Stuff makes the world go 'round,
Dre, especially our world.

06:36.397 --> 06:37.896
We're ad men.
- Mm.

06:37.898 --> 06:39.831
- And women.
- Amen, sister.

06:39.833 --> 06:42.534
Do I seem like someone you
should be that comfortable with?

06:42.536 --> 06:46.004
Okay, g-guys, look, look, I'm
trying to start a new tradition.

06:46.006 --> 06:48.240
Ah, traditions.
Mm-hmm.

06:48.242 --> 06:51.276
Yeah, Phillip took
all of ours in the divorce.

06:51.278 --> 06:54.379
Holidays are
the hardest times... that...

06:54.381 --> 06:56.548
- [ Murmurs ]
- Gut-wrenching loneliness...

06:56.550 --> 06:58.683
Sadness...

06:58.685 --> 07:01.186
Settling like fresh fallen snow.

07:01.188 --> 07:03.688
No snow plow coming for me.

07:03.690 --> 07:06.057
- [ Clears throat ]
- Just cold...

07:06.059 --> 07:07.926
Frozen.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.060
Winter's a-coming!

07:09.062 --> 07:10.862
Okay, o-okay,
d-Daphne, Daphne.

07:10.864 --> 07:14.032
Okay, look, would you like
to come have dinner with us?

07:14.034 --> 07:16.368
What? I don't need
your damn pity invite.

07:16.370 --> 07:18.303
And no matter what,
I know my Christmas

07:18.305 --> 07:20.138
is gonna be better than Lucy's.

07:20.140 --> 07:21.540
W-what,
because I'm Jewish?

07:21.542 --> 07:22.974
No, because you're boring.

07:22.976 --> 07:24.443
I didn't know you were Jewish.

07:24.445 --> 07:26.945
Ha!
You are growing on me.

07:26.947 --> 07:29.381
♪♪

07:29.383 --> 07:30.449
[ Footsteps approaching ]

07:30.451 --> 07:32.017
Ruby: So!

07:33.253 --> 07:37.122
Lady Diana,
how's that volunteering going?

07:37.124 --> 07:38.924
Just because
I'm not volunteering

07:38.926 --> 07:41.560
every second of the day doesn't
mean I'm not volunteering.

07:41.562 --> 07:43.829
[ Laughs ]
Did you even sign up?

07:43.831 --> 07:45.096
Yes.

07:45.098 --> 07:46.665
Did you pass
the background check?

07:46.667 --> 07:47.599
Yes, of course.

07:47.601 --> 07:48.934
They don't run one!

07:48.936 --> 07:50.168
Charlatan.

07:50.170 --> 07:51.736
I...
Eh!

07:51.738 --> 07:53.905
Eh-eh.

07:53.907 --> 07:55.507
<i>This whole thing started</i>

07:55.509 --> 07:57.576
<i>because pops convinced
bow and me</i>

07:57.578 --> 08:00.745
<i>we needed to teach
our bratty kids a lesson,</i>

08:00.747 --> 08:03.348
<i>but looking around,
we didn't see any bratty kids.</i>

08:03.350 --> 08:06.418
♪ Here we are,
arms around each other ♪

08:06.420 --> 08:07.752
♪ The quiet scene ♪
boop!

08:07.754 --> 08:09.821
♪ Pretty lights all over ♪

08:09.823 --> 08:14.893
♪ Snow is falling,
and everyone is here tonight ♪

08:15.796 --> 08:17.929
♪ Iaaa ♪

08:17.931 --> 08:22.667
♪ It's a merry Christmas ♪

08:22.669 --> 08:24.870
♪ All the bells are ringing
♪ hey, babe? Yeah.

08:24.872 --> 08:27.873
Have you seen the adorableness
of our children?

08:27.875 --> 08:30.709
Jack has frosting on his nose.

08:30.711 --> 08:32.310
Shut up.
[ Laughs ]

08:32.312 --> 08:34.212
My god.
Where's junior?

08:34.214 --> 08:35.547
I haven't seen him in a while.

08:35.549 --> 08:36.648
Me either.
Gosh...

08:36.650 --> 08:38.650
I don't remember
the last time I saw him.

08:38.652 --> 08:39.718
It feels like forever.

08:39.720 --> 08:40.852
Kind of miss the little fella.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.654
I know, right?
Mm.

08:42.656 --> 08:45.390
Oh, god, his smile
can really light up a room.

08:45.392 --> 08:46.791
Aww.
It's like bing!

08:46.793 --> 08:48.326
Little curly-head sucker.

08:48.328 --> 08:49.661
Let's go.

08:49.663 --> 08:53.231
♪♪

08:53.233 --> 08:56.301
And then carry over
the two, and...

08:56.303 --> 08:59.004
Oh. Hey.

08:59.006 --> 09:01.072
Hello, mama, papa.

09:01.074 --> 09:04.042
Oh, my god.
You... you guys are so...

09:04.044 --> 09:06.144
Maybe we should reconsider.

09:06.146 --> 09:07.913
Nope!
Don't fall for it.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.247
They're trying to trick you

09:09.249 --> 09:11.182
into forgetting
what monsters they are.

09:11.184 --> 09:14.719
Old-school Christmas...
One gift.

09:14.721 --> 09:19.724
♪♪

09:19.726 --> 09:21.393
You can come out now.

09:21.395 --> 09:24.095
Any chance
at a real Christmas is over.

09:24.097 --> 09:28.066
Might as well make our lists...
Our sad, one-gift lists.

09:28.068 --> 09:31.069
I'm not coming out.
Never say die!

09:31.071 --> 09:34.339
♪♪

09:38.278 --> 09:39.578
Ugh.

09:40.914 --> 09:42.013
Ugh!

09:44.017 --> 09:46.351
Okay.
Hey, bow, what are you doing?

09:46.353 --> 09:48.119
It's 5:30.
We haven't even had dinner yet.

09:48.121 --> 09:50.021
Yes, I know,
but I need to go to sleep

09:50.023 --> 09:51.957
so that I can wake up
at 3:00 A.M.

09:51.959 --> 09:53.525
To get to the homeless shelter.

09:53.527 --> 09:55.627
[ Sighs ]
Doesn't matter anyway.

09:55.629 --> 09:57.195
I'm not gonna be able to sleep

09:57.197 --> 09:59.598
'cause all I'm thinking about is
this whole one-gift thing.

09:59.600 --> 10:00.932
Uh...
[ Paper rustles ]

10:00.934 --> 10:02.434
Have you seen
their Christmas lists?

10:03.270 --> 10:04.603
"Wizard cape.

10:04.605 --> 10:07.772
Would prefer standard,
but waist-length is okay."

10:09.142 --> 10:11.376
Oh, my god.
This is so sad.

10:11.378 --> 10:13.211
I know.

10:13.213 --> 10:14.946
Jack wants "kold kuts".
[ Sighing ] I know.

10:14.948 --> 10:17.148
With two k's!
Uh, yeah.

10:17.150 --> 10:18.617
Dre, do you think
we were too harsh

10:18.619 --> 10:19.918
with the kids with the presents?

10:19.920 --> 10:22.220
[ Sighs ] Maybe.
Mm.

10:22.222 --> 10:24.322
Look, I don't want my kids
waking up on Christmas

10:24.324 --> 10:25.757
disappointed like I did.

10:25.759 --> 10:29.427
Every year, I told pops I wanted
Clay-colored riedell skates,

10:29.429 --> 10:32.897
and every year,
he gave me food from the fridge.

10:32.899 --> 10:36.434
Mm-hmm. I had to borrow my
cousin's plastic skates.

10:36.436 --> 10:38.937
<i>I couldn't go two feet
without falling.</i>

10:38.939 --> 10:41.840
<i>I was high-stepping
like a Clydesdale.</i>

10:41.842 --> 10:45.343
No one wanted me
on their skate crew.

10:45.345 --> 10:49.114
My poor,
little crewless Clydesdale.

10:49.116 --> 10:50.782
[ Sighs ] Dre?

10:50.784 --> 10:51.950
Hmm?

10:51.952 --> 10:53.985
Do you think maybe...

10:53.987 --> 10:56.287
Maybe we could get the kids
just, like, a few more gifts...

10:56.289 --> 10:58.023
Not as many
as we were gonna get 'em,

10:58.025 --> 10:59.691
but just, like,
you know, more than one.

10:59.693 --> 11:01.259
And maybe some extra for junior.

11:02.462 --> 11:05.063
He was my favorite.

11:08.468 --> 11:10.669
Uh, what happened
to "never say die!"?

11:10.671 --> 11:13.505
I got bit by a relentless,
orange spider.

11:13.507 --> 11:15.640
I may actually die.

11:15.642 --> 11:16.641
Hey, kids, listen up.

11:16.643 --> 11:18.009
[ Gasps ] Junior!

11:18.011 --> 11:20.145
Oh, my goodness.
Where have you been?!

11:20.147 --> 11:22.280
Sweetheart, did you get taller?!

11:22.282 --> 11:24.282
Son, come here, come here!

11:24.284 --> 11:26.484
Oh, my god.
I missed you, little buddy!

11:26.486 --> 11:27.485
How are you?!

11:27.487 --> 11:29.354
Not so good.
I got bit by a poisonous...

11:29.356 --> 11:30.488
Okay, not now. Not now.

11:30.490 --> 11:31.623
I have something important
to say.

11:31.625 --> 11:33.191
Okay.
Kids...

11:33.193 --> 11:34.659
We're bringing Christmas back.

11:34.661 --> 11:35.860
[ All cheering ]

11:35.862 --> 11:37.162
- Ah, shh, shh!
- Shhhh!

11:37.164 --> 11:38.663
Secretly.

11:38.665 --> 11:40.231
Nobody tell pops.

11:40.233 --> 11:41.566
Okay.

11:41.568 --> 11:42.634
[ Chuckles ]

11:42.636 --> 11:44.903
Please help me.

11:44.905 --> 11:46.671
So cold.

11:46.673 --> 11:49.708
Insides turning to jelly!

11:49.710 --> 11:51.276
Oh!

11:55.582 --> 11:56.981
<i>I was having lunch
with my colleagues the next day</i>

11:56.983 --> 11:58.883
<i>when bow made
an unexpected appearance.</i>

11:58.885 --> 12:00.251
- Oh, hey, babe.
- Hi.

12:00.253 --> 12:01.653
- Everything okay?
- Well...

12:01.655 --> 12:03.755
You know, w-what are you doing
here looking like this?

12:03.757 --> 12:04.856
[ Chuckles ]
This is my job.

12:04.858 --> 12:06.024
Rainbow!
Wow!

12:06.026 --> 12:07.325
Why don't you come on in?

12:07.327 --> 12:08.526
Have a seat.
Yeah, come and sit.

12:08.528 --> 12:12.197
This is, uh, Daphne, and this
is, um [Fingers snaps]

12:12.199 --> 12:13.199
Doesn't matter.

12:14.201 --> 12:15.867
Are you okay?
Because you don't...

12:15.869 --> 12:17.535
Uh, how do I say this?...
Uh, look okay.

12:17.537 --> 12:19.003
Oh. No, no, she's fine.
She's fine.

12:19.005 --> 12:20.672
She just volunteered today
at the homeless shelter.

12:20.674 --> 12:21.840
Why?
Why?

12:21.842 --> 12:23.675
Oh, she was obviously there
scouting out organs.

12:23.677 --> 12:26.678
N-no.
Because volunteering is nice.

12:26.680 --> 12:28.279
No, that makes no sense.

12:28.281 --> 12:31.082
Babe...
Why are you here?

12:31.084 --> 12:32.283
'Cause I thought
I could come here

12:32.285 --> 12:33.518
and we could
have lunch together.

12:33.520 --> 12:35.220
Oh, my god, of course!
You're hungry.

12:35.222 --> 12:37.088
Lucy [Fingers snap]
Give her your lunch.

12:37.090 --> 12:40.859
Oh. Oh, my god!
I do look awful!

12:40.861 --> 12:43.528
God, I was just trying to do
something nice for Christmas.

12:43.530 --> 12:45.530
Christmas doesn't always
work out the way you want.

12:45.532 --> 12:47.132
Oh, my god.
If I had my way,

12:47.134 --> 12:49.100
Phillip and I
would be popping "x"

12:49.102 --> 12:50.769
and rolling around
in cranberry sauce

12:50.771 --> 12:52.137
like the old days.

12:52.139 --> 12:54.105
Pre-holiday divorce...
That's a rookie mistake.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.474
Early October
is when you want to file,

12:56.476 --> 12:58.109
especially in New Hampshire.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.878
The foliage
around the Concord courthouse

12:59.880 --> 13:01.813
is absolutely fabulous.

13:01.815 --> 13:03.248
I'll keep that in mind

13:03.250 --> 13:05.817
as I'm trying to eat
a 25-pound Turkey by myself.

13:05.819 --> 13:06.985
Wait, by yourself?

13:06.987 --> 13:08.586
You can't be by yourself
on Christmas.

13:08.588 --> 13:10.288
Why don't... why don't you
come over to our house?

13:10.290 --> 13:11.556
Babe, she's not interested.

13:11.558 --> 13:12.991
I most certainly am.

13:12.993 --> 13:14.325
Thank you, Dre's wife.

13:14.327 --> 13:15.994
Nobody here had the decency.

13:15.996 --> 13:18.062
N-n-now, h-hold up.
Wait a minute.

13:18.064 --> 13:21.299
Daphne, I invited you Tuesday.

13:21.301 --> 13:24.402
Does lying
make you feel like a man, Dre?

13:24.404 --> 13:26.805
I...

13:26.807 --> 13:29.974
<i>So, to get to the fun
of our secret Christmas Eve,</i>

13:29.976 --> 13:32.443
<i>all we had to do
was endure pops'</i>

13:32.445 --> 13:34.746
<i>old-school
Christmas Eve dinner.</i>

13:34.748 --> 13:36.247
All right, everybody, dig in.

13:36.249 --> 13:38.516
This is a Christmas Eve dinner
the way god intended it...

13:38.518 --> 13:39.784
Fresh out the box.

13:39.786 --> 13:41.653
Are we sure
this is what god intended?

13:41.655 --> 13:44.756
Baby girl, everything tastes
better straight out the box.

13:44.758 --> 13:45.824
Now, who wants a leg and a wing?

13:45.826 --> 13:47.492
Is it organic?

13:47.494 --> 13:49.861
Why aren't we having
regular Christmas Eve dinner?

13:49.863 --> 13:51.830
Boy, if you don't hush up
and eat your food...

13:51.832 --> 13:54.032
Okay, everybody, just eat up.
There's Turkey in the hamper.

13:54.034 --> 13:56.267
No, no, no, baby, he's right.

13:56.269 --> 13:59.470
Why are we eating
cold chicken out of a box?

13:59.472 --> 14:00.738
[ Muffled ] Excuse me?

14:00.740 --> 14:01.873
I want to know!

14:01.875 --> 14:03.775
Why are you making us do this?

14:03.777 --> 14:05.276
I'm not<i> making</i> you do this.

14:05.278 --> 14:06.945
We<i> get</i> to do this!

14:06.947 --> 14:08.780
I'm going to go order Sushi.

14:08.782 --> 14:10.849
Sit down, little girl.

14:10.851 --> 14:12.383
This is Christmas Eve dinner,

14:12.385 --> 14:14.452
and you are going to
appreciate it.

14:14.454 --> 14:16.454
You see this mess here?

14:16.456 --> 14:17.689
This is "stuff" talk.

14:17.691 --> 14:18.723
There's stuffing?

14:18.725 --> 14:20.291
How does my kids wanting to have

14:20.293 --> 14:22.293
a decent dinner at Christmas
have anything to do

14:22.295 --> 14:23.695
with me buying them
too much stuff?

14:23.697 --> 14:25.730
This is what you had.
You turned out all right.

14:25.732 --> 14:28.666
I turned out all right
in spite of all of this!

14:28.668 --> 14:30.368
Sweetie, just ignore him.

14:30.370 --> 14:31.703
Seriously,
we have the secret Christmas.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.137
No! You know what?

14:33.139 --> 14:36.074
We tried Christmas your way,
and it sucks!

14:36.076 --> 14:37.375
Oh, you're too good now?

14:37.377 --> 14:39.043
Oh. You got a little
money in your pocket,

14:39.045 --> 14:40.845
and now my traditional
Christmas Eve dinner

14:40.847 --> 14:42.180
isn't good enough for you.

14:42.182 --> 14:44.816
Well, fine.
Go have your Sushi.

14:44.818 --> 14:45.917
Thank you.

14:45.919 --> 14:47.886
Yellowfin tuna?
You know it.

14:47.888 --> 14:49.687
Dre:
It's not about Sushi, pops.

14:49.689 --> 14:51.723
It's about us
doing things our way,

14:51.725 --> 14:53.424
so we're gonna go upstairs,

14:53.426 --> 14:56.194
and we're gonna open up
all the presents that I bought

14:56.196 --> 14:58.830
because I'm proud of the way
that we do Christmas...

14:58.832 --> 15:00.798
Secretly, in the closet!

15:00.800 --> 15:04.035
Everybody, up!
Let's go open some stuff!

15:04.037 --> 15:05.670
[ Claps ]
Come on! Let's get our stuff on!

15:05.672 --> 15:07.906
Okay, Christmas!

15:07.908 --> 15:09.741
Whoa, babe.

15:09.743 --> 15:11.442
If you're upset,
we don't have to do this now.

15:11.444 --> 15:13.511
Oh, no, no, no, no. We can
wait until Christmas morning.

15:13.513 --> 15:14.913
We're gonna do this right now.
Okay, I...

15:14.915 --> 15:17.582
We are going to celebrate
Christmas, damn it, okay?!

15:17.584 --> 15:19.117
- Wow.
- Here's a gift.

15:19.119 --> 15:21.352
Here's a gift. Here's a gift.
There's your gift!

15:21.354 --> 15:22.453
- Okay.
- Stuff!

15:22.455 --> 15:24.055
Now, get to it!

15:24.057 --> 15:26.124
A merry...
Christmas.

15:26.126 --> 15:27.592
Mm-hmm.
Yes!

15:27.594 --> 15:29.560
Uh... oh.

15:29.562 --> 15:31.129
A 6.
What's wrong?

15:31.131 --> 15:32.430
Nothing. [ Sighs ]

15:32.432 --> 15:35.199
Except I kind of asked
for a 6s, but it's cool.

15:35.201 --> 15:37.268
I mean,
how are you supposed to know?

15:37.270 --> 15:39.270
Except for the part where
I wrote it down for you, but...

15:39.272 --> 15:42.040
I can't believe this!

15:42.042 --> 15:44.142
[ Sighs ] And what
is wrong with you?!

15:44.144 --> 15:47.412
I disappeared myself
for a gift card to j.Crew?!

15:47.414 --> 15:49.113
You took money I could use
every place

15:49.115 --> 15:51.282
and turned it into money
I could use one place.

15:51.284 --> 15:55.286
So... Jack has more presents
than I do?!

15:55.288 --> 15:57.588
Okay.
Shots fired.

15:57.590 --> 16:00.124
You're jealous of a goldfish?

16:00.126 --> 16:02.593
A daily chore
that ends in heartbreak?!

16:02.595 --> 16:04.228
What is happening?!

16:04.230 --> 16:05.830
We're getting stuff
that we don't like.

16:05.832 --> 16:07.398
Are you not picking up on that?

16:07.400 --> 16:08.499
You guys!

16:08.501 --> 16:10.068
I stood up for you guys!

16:10.070 --> 16:11.836
I went against my father

16:11.838 --> 16:14.739
and every tradition
that I had growing up!

16:14.741 --> 16:17.275
For what?! For this?!

16:17.277 --> 16:18.443
Okay.

16:18.445 --> 16:20.445
So...

16:20.447 --> 16:22.413
Gift receipts?

16:22.415 --> 16:23.881
No, Diane.

16:27.854 --> 16:31.422
All right.
I did it.

16:31.424 --> 16:34.325
I ruined the old-school
Christmas and secret Christmas.

16:34.327 --> 16:37.929
Can't wait to see
what you do to new year's.

16:37.931 --> 16:39.163
You know, I tried to blame you,

16:39.165 --> 16:41.799
I tried to blame the kids,
but all this falls on me.

16:41.801 --> 16:43.101
Well...

16:43.103 --> 16:44.802
Nobody's disagreeing with you.

16:44.804 --> 16:47.638
You know, a-as fathers...

16:47.640 --> 16:51.075
We try to give our kids
more than we had.

16:52.645 --> 16:54.645
Sometimes that just
isn't the best thing.

16:54.647 --> 16:57.715
♪♪

17:05.859 --> 17:07.792
<i>So, Christmas morning
was bright and sunny outside,</i>

17:07.794 --> 17:09.727
<i>but not inside.</i>

17:09.729 --> 17:11.696
[ Sighs ] Do you think
we'll still get stockings?

17:11.698 --> 17:13.398
What is wrong with you?

17:13.400 --> 17:15.900
For some weird reason,
dad's boss is here.

17:15.902 --> 17:16.901
Did she bring presents?

17:16.903 --> 17:18.636
She did not.
Well, hi! Hello!

17:18.638 --> 17:20.371
Oh, my goodness.
So nice you came!

17:20.373 --> 17:22.707
[ Chuckles nervously ]
Dre will be right back,

17:22.709 --> 17:25.643
but, please, uh, join our, um,
our chr... our Christmas.

17:25.645 --> 17:28.880
Wow, uh,
thank you for inviting me

17:28.882 --> 17:32.550
to this wonderfully festive
and heartwarming environment.

17:32.552 --> 17:35.219
D-do the kids
not have presents?

17:35.221 --> 17:36.754
Our dad threw them away
before we woke up.

17:36.756 --> 17:39.057
[ Laughing nervously ]

17:39.059 --> 17:41.826
Ha! That sounds so much worse
than it is.

17:41.828 --> 17:43.161
Well, here's what happened.

17:43.163 --> 17:45.196
So, Dre had a screaming match
with his dad

17:45.198 --> 17:47.031
over the fried
Christmas chicken,

17:47.033 --> 17:49.400
and then we went upstairs
to have our secret Christmas

17:49.402 --> 17:51.402
in the closet
and our hamper Turkey,

17:51.404 --> 17:53.271
and Dre had already
thrown his dirty underwear

17:53.273 --> 17:54.338
[chuckles] On top
of the Turkey, so...

17:54.340 --> 17:55.673
[ Inhales deeply ]
And then the goldfish died.

17:55.675 --> 17:57.275
She did?!

17:57.944 --> 18:01.446
Ooh. A-anyway, um, we're all
just trying to, you know,

18:01.448 --> 18:03.781
rally and have a nice...

18:03.783 --> 18:04.949
Normal Christmas.

18:04.951 --> 18:08.052
♪ Happy birthday ♪

18:08.054 --> 18:09.787
♪ Black Jesus ♪

18:09.789 --> 18:11.255
Black Jesus?
♪ Happy birthday ♪

18:11.257 --> 18:13.024
♪ Black Jesus ♪ yes, she...
Calls him that.

18:13.026 --> 18:16.861
[ Sighs ] ♪ happy birthday,
dear redeemer king ♪

18:16.863 --> 18:19.530
♪ Happy birthday
to you ♪

18:19.532 --> 18:20.631
[ Blows ]

18:20.633 --> 18:22.934
You know,
I'm just gonna go grab Chinese

18:22.936 --> 18:25.069
with the sad Jewish
girl from work. Oh.

18:25.071 --> 18:27.405
♪ For he's a jolly good savior ♪

18:27.407 --> 18:29.040
♪ For he's a jolly good savior ♪ please,
uh, Dre will be so sad he missed you.

18:29.042 --> 18:31.042
♪ For he's a jolly good savior ♪
I'll walk... why are you running?

18:31.044 --> 18:32.710
♪ Who nobody can renounce ♪

18:32.712 --> 18:34.912
Come on!
♪ Who nobody can renounce ♪

18:34.914 --> 18:36.781
♪ Who nobody can renounce ♪

18:36.783 --> 18:38.382
♪ For he's... ♪

18:38.384 --> 18:40.151
All right, pops, what's up?

18:42.622 --> 18:44.388
I hate church's chicken.

18:44.390 --> 18:46.224
What?

18:46.226 --> 18:48.493
Don't get me wrong.
It's chicken.

18:48.495 --> 18:52.096
It's fried in delicious batter,
but I hate it.

18:52.098 --> 18:54.232
Then why did you talk it up
every year

18:54.234 --> 18:56.501
and make it
our Christmas tradition?

18:56.503 --> 18:58.169
Because it was the best
I could do,

18:58.171 --> 18:59.570
and I was so embarrassed,

18:59.572 --> 19:02.440
I tried to sell it
as the best that ever was.

19:02.442 --> 19:03.674
[ Sighs ]

19:03.676 --> 19:05.676
Pops, you just could've said so.

19:05.678 --> 19:07.178
And what's that conversation
look like?

19:07.180 --> 19:09.847
"Listen, son,
I work a minimum-wage job,"

19:09.849 --> 19:11.415
and I can barely
keep the lights on.

19:11.417 --> 19:14.752
"So, here are some pickles.
Merry Christmas."

19:14.754 --> 19:18.289
Well, maybe not exactly
in those words.

19:18.291 --> 19:20.258
I-I see what you're trying
to do for your kids,

19:20.260 --> 19:21.292
and I respect it.

19:21.294 --> 19:23.294
I just think
you're trying to do too much.

19:23.296 --> 19:24.962
Now, maybe I went
a little overboard

19:24.964 --> 19:26.631
with the old-school Christmas...
Mm-hmm.

19:26.633 --> 19:28.933
But your new-school Christmas
ain't exactly working, either.

19:28.935 --> 19:31.369
[ Chuckles ]

19:31.371 --> 19:33.271
Well, there's always Kwanzaa.

19:33.273 --> 19:34.639
[ Scoffs ]
Boy, you ain't got no sense.

19:34.641 --> 19:36.107
[ Laughs ]

19:36.109 --> 19:39.343
But look here.
You're a decent dad.

19:39.345 --> 19:41.479
♪ So, this is Christmas ♪

19:41.481 --> 19:43.981
Merry Christmas.

19:43.983 --> 19:45.483
♪ And what have you done? ♪ but
I didn't get you anything.

19:45.485 --> 19:47.285
Yes, you did.

19:49.222 --> 19:50.655
♪ Another year older ♪

19:50.657 --> 19:53.524
You know, this...
This feels pickle-heavy.

19:53.526 --> 19:54.859
Boy, if you don't open that gift...
[ Laughs ]

19:54.861 --> 19:57.361
♪ And a new one just begun ♪
I'm gonna open your head.

19:58.865 --> 20:01.933
♪ And so, this is Christmas ♪
huh?

20:03.469 --> 20:05.136
♪ I hope you have fun ♪
my skates?!

20:05.138 --> 20:07.038
And this here is your crew.

20:08.374 --> 20:12.643
♪ The near and the dear ones ♪

20:12.645 --> 20:14.645
♪ The old and the young ♪

20:14.647 --> 20:17.682
Thanks, pops.

20:17.684 --> 20:20.351
♪ A very merry Christmas ♪ dad,
we're sorry we were monsters.

20:20.353 --> 20:23.321
You make it feel like Christmas
every day...

20:23.323 --> 20:25.189
♪ And a happy new year ♪ ...And we're
sorry that we don't show you that.

20:25.191 --> 20:27.592
I'm also just grateful
to be alive.

20:27.594 --> 20:30.228
♪ Let's hope it's a good one ♪
I love my goldfish, daddy.

20:30.230 --> 20:31.662
God rest her soul.

20:31.664 --> 20:33.864
Diane: Look, I'm not saying
you should give me less, but...

20:33.866 --> 20:37.568
♪ Without any fear ♪ ...I'll try
to start appreciating it more.

20:37.570 --> 20:40.404
♪ So this is Christmas ♪
try... no promises.

20:40.406 --> 20:43.574
Well, it's no
"god bless us, everyone"...

20:43.576 --> 20:45.276
♪ And what have we done? ♪
But I'll take it.

20:45.278 --> 20:47.111
[ Chuckles ]
Come on, give me some love.

20:47.113 --> 20:48.246
Give me some love.

20:48.248 --> 20:50.448
♪ Another year over ♪

20:50.450 --> 20:52.450
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

20:52.452 --> 20:54.385
♪ And a new one just begun ♪

20:54.387 --> 20:55.486
[ Laughter ]

21:00.793 --> 21:02.026
All right, I think I'm getting
the hang of this.

21:02.028 --> 21:03.694
[ All shout ]
Whoo! It's all right.

21:03.696 --> 21:05.630
Why would you ask
for a pair of skates

21:05.632 --> 21:06.530
if you never learned
how to skate?!

21:06.532 --> 21:07.898
[ All shouting ]

21:07.900 --> 21:09.767
Okay, bow, can you help me?!

21:09.769 --> 21:10.901
Listen to 'em jingle.

21:10.903 --> 21:12.570
[ Bracelets jingling ]
Jangle, jingle!

21:12.572 --> 21:15.640
Baby Jesus has leftovers!
Who wants cake?!

21:15.642 --> 21:17.041
Me! Me!
Me! Me!

21:17.043 --> 21:18.943
[ Pants tearing ]
Aah! Aah!

21:18.945 --> 21:20.778
Okay, save me some cake!

21:20.780 --> 21:23.047
Ow! Ooh!
